## AUDIT FINDINGS REQUIRING IMMEDIATE ACTION

**BLOCKING ISSUES (do not deploy to production without fixes):**

1. **Amendment Period Validation Missing** — All 16 engines recommend claims without checking if the FY is within amendment window (TAA 1953 s 170). Expired claims will be rejected by ATO. FIX: Integrate `amendment_period_tracker.checkAmendmentPeriod()` call before outputting any retrospective recommendation.

2. **Division 7A Distributable Surplus Not Checked** — Engine assumes all deemed dividend is payable but s 109Y caps deemed div at company distributable surplus. Can overstate liability. FIX: Add `calculateDistributableSurplus()` check before final Div7A output.

3. **Tax Rate Versioning Not Propagated** — Only PDF reports include rate version + fetch timestamp. API responses and dashboard do NOT. Creates audit trail gap. FIX: Add `rateVersion` and `ratesFetchedAt` to all EngineResult output types; include in API responses.

**HIGH-PRIORITY (fix within 2 sprints):**

4. **Rate Change Detection Missing** — System has no mechanism to flag stale analyses when ATO publishes new rates. Analysis from 2023 using $20K write-off threshold may be wrong if threshold changed. FIX: Deploy rate-change-monitor agent (agents/rate_change_monitor/AGENT.md) with weekly ATO scraping; mark results >90 days old as needing re-run.

5. **Compliance Audit Findings (32 items)** — 6 marked CRITICAL (Division 7A, R&D offset, Loss tests). Run findings against test validators (.claude/hooks/validators/) on every analysis and block output if CRITICAL issue detected.